%N A385315 Smallest number k such that both k^n - 1 and k^n + 1 have n prime factors, counted with repetitions.
%H A385315 Jean-Marc Rebert, <a href="/A385315/a385315_2.pdf">Factorizations of k^n-1 and k^n+1</a>
%F A385315 a(n) >= max(A368162(n), A368163(n)). - _Daniel Suteu_, Sep 02 2025
%e A385315 a(1) = 4, because 4^1 - 1 = 3 and 4^1 + 1 = 5, and no lesser number has this property.
